stylometry: Some of the advantages include being able to see the detailed results before making an investment which essentially saves a business money both in the short and long term run. A simulation model provides highly detailed results - so it is informative and useful in decision making. A simulation can also be a projection of many factors; and gives a business options; for example using a range of values in the input for the simulation to make a decison - in some cases we have even used the value 0 in the "possibly quantities to try" which essentially would be to 'do nothing' so clearly a business has options, and can see results of those options in a simulation model.
